subSubSection.paragraph:
Female.
Similar to the male in shape and size, differing by the following characteristics: The color tones are darker than the male but keep the same pattern (
Figs. 4A–B
). Tegmina not reaching the posterior border of the metanotum, widely separated from each other (
Figs. 4A
; 
5A
). Tympanum present only on the external face of the foretibia, ovoid and elongated, occupying a third of the tibia outer surface (
Figs. 5B–C
). Left hind tibia with four spurs on each dorsal margin (
Fig. 5I
); right hind tibia with four spurs on the inner dorsal margin, and three spurs on the outer dorsal margin (
Fig. 5H
). Epiproct ovoid, with rounded posterior margin (
Fig. 5E
). Ovipositor almost straight, apex of the valves pointed, with sharp angles (
Fig. 5J
), and triangular in dorsal view (
Fig. 5K
). Subgenital plate trapezoid, apex truncated (
Fig. 5F
).

